00:44:43,660 --> 00:44:47,660
They are trained on billions of highly recomposable, low-binding fragments.

438
00:44:47,900 --> 00:44:55,620
So if our future cognitive engines are fundamentally built upon the linguistic debris of the algorithmic feed...

439
00:44:55,620 --> 00:45:02,120
Are we inadvertently locking our entire intellectual trajectory into a permanent selection regime?

440
00:45:02,120 --> 00:45:13,260
Can a machine intelligence, trained on the aesthetics of pseudobinding, ever generate the self-imposed, rigorous logic required to achieve true closure?

441
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:24,360
Or is the future of human thought, outsourced to the machine, mathematically destined to be perfectly formatted, infinitely shareable, and structurally hollow?

442
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:28,160
It is the ultimate stress test of Flyxion's variables.

443
00:45:28,940 --> 00:45:33,760
Can the machine ever learn to engineer the irregular binding edges of the jigsaw puzzle?

444
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:38,900
Or is it mathematically constrained to only ever manufacture Lego bricks?

